<h2>
    <strong>Oregon Fishing Regulations You Must Know</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Fishing regulations in Oregon are strictly enforced to protect fish populations and preserve the sport for future generations.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Important Rules:</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>License Required:</strong> All anglers over 12 must have a valid Oregon fishing license.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Harvest Tags:</strong> Additional Columbia River Basin Endorsement is needed for salmon.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Daily Limits:</strong> Usually 2 sockeye per day (subject to change).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Barbless Hooks Only:</strong> Mandatory in certain rivers.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Always check the <strong>Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife (ODFW)</strong> website for the latest updates.
</p>
